Now... for actual content.<br>
<br>
An economics lesson to spellless people.<br>
<br>
Please realize that the people who got these spells in the first place got to where they are without assistance, without the 'class defining' spells you crave.<br>
<br>
On other servers, the 'top-of-the-pecking-order' guilds (sounds a lot worse than uber guild, but every time I say that, someone pisses and moans) SELL these spells to pay for peridots and coffins.<br>
<br>
Now i'm sure there's some clueless monkey fucker out there that is saying 'but jeez, coffins are less than 80pp for the stackers and peridots are only 10.5pp each... how much could they spend?'<br>
<br>
Let me break it down:<br>
<br>
36 man raid. 7.5 hrs<br>
<br>
Aegolism (group) for 36 people (6 groups) at 4 peridots/group= 72 peridots for the night.<br>
<br>
Assuming that every pulling monk will die once an hour (7 times/raid, 3 monks) (a VERY conservative estimate=21 peridots to rebuff)<br>
<br>
Rune V every 15 mins on main mezzing enchanter= 30 peridots<br>
<br>
Rune V every hour or so on 2 other chanters (figure 5x each) = 10 peridots<br>
<br>
Chain Rune V on Main Tank during a minor wipeout (15 casts, 15 peridots)<br>
<br>
A minor wipeout (half of raid dead) rebuff for Aegolism= 20 peridots.<br>
<br>
Dragonbane/Giantbane (Hsagra's Wrath/Porlos' Fury) cast 20x by each of 6 Wizards = 240 peridots.<br>
<br>
So JUST peridots on a conservative raid is ~ 408 peridots (more than 14 stacks) = around 4200pp. That's if you WIN and don't have mobs that don't require MORE of this.<br>
<br>
Take a north TOV raid... where if you have a streak of bad luck, you lose 2-3 monks every pull and each wizard casts Dragonbane 100, 120 times... you can triple or quadruple this number. 17000pp for a win. Add in a coffin wipeout - 40x75pp (perfect combo of faction/charisma, easy to get now) = 3000pp PLUS the cost to rebuff.<br>
<br>
On FV, there are no twinks, really. There is no easy way to make cash with a high-demand item because eventually the demand will drop off. My old guild used to keep the coffin fund full by selling froglok crowns. These guilds have to get money somehow to pay for this... the cash drops in the raid zones RARELY cover the cost of raiding there (with one notable exception).<br>
<br>
So, before you call it gouging, please realize that the high level guilds are living under the exact same constraints as you are with this economy. <p>Nakath<BR>
